title: For Sale:  Like-new Glock 26 with Night Sights
postcontent:
This handgun was given to me as a gift, only shot once, and never used otherwise.  Comes with night sights, one slightly extended magazine, and full kit.  In excellent condition!  Buyer pays for background check.

Often referred to as the "Pocket Glock" or "Baby Glock," the Glock 26 debuted in 1995 as the perfect concealed carry pistol. Only about six and half inches long and four inches tall, the Glock 26 is simple and lightweight in a conceal carry holster. Backed by the quality and history of excellence carried by Glock, the Glock 26 remains a popular subcompact semi-automatic pistol nearly 20 years after its debut and is primarily used by civilians interested in concealed carry.

The Glock 26's size only allows for a two-finger pistol grip but its double-stacked magazine still carries ten rounds of 9mm ammunition. Not just a smaller version of its predecessors, the Glock 26 was created through an extensive redesign of the frame, spring assembly and locking block. Featuring no less than three independent safety systems, the Glock line utilizes two internal, automatic safeties as well as an external integrated trigger safety. The internal mechanisms are comprised of both a drop safety and a firing pin safety. Once the trigger is squeezed, the three safety mechanisms are automatically disengaged one after the other. When the trigger is released, they automatically reactivate.

title: For Sale:  "SHOTGUN" Pistol German made & FREE barrel insert (THE TRUTH)
postcontent:
THE TRUTH about flare guns and what he is not telling you!

As he stated, a flare gun is legal to carry concealed.
You can buy inserts to put in them.

But what he is not telling you is once one of those inserts are put into the flare gun, it makes it a weapon. And in the eye of the ATF it is considered "Other" by definition.
This means you must submit a form thru ATF and a fee of $200 to legally carry this as a weapon.

So the $250 flare gun price, and $200 tax stamp, which would have to be paid for EACH insert, is more then what you can just buy a Judge for.

Plus you wouldn't be able to carry it concealed unless you had a permit.

Bottom line people.....don't listen to these dumb asses that circumvent the law to make a buck. Do your research before an idiot like this lands your ass in jail.

Have fun, and be safe!

title: For Sale:  Tavor FLEx swivel by GEAR HEAD WORKS
postcontent:
I have a new in package FLEx swivel for the IWI Tavor rifle. I ordered one, and received two. They retail for $55 from GEAR HEAD WORKS. I can ship this item to you, with payment made throgh Paypal. Price includes shipping. The following text is from the GEAR HEAD WORKS website.

The last photo shows the part installed on the Tavor.

 FLEx stands for Fulcrum Located Extra swivel. It provides a centralized location for use with a single point sling or just an additional swivel location for a 2 point. It can be mounted on either side and with the swivel towards the front or rear of the gun. It replaces the plastic factory port cover very easily. But its greatest feature may not be the extra swivel you gain but it also seals off the port from escaping gases that tend to leak out of the factory cover and hit you right in the face. This phenomenon has become known as "Tavor face" and leaves you with black smudges on your cheek and shooting glasses. This problem is exacerbated with suppressor use. This is truly a must have if you are running a suppressor.
